  "nursesNote": "Patients with serious mental illness have higher rates of physical illness and a shorter lifespan, due to medication side effects, poor access to care, lifestyle factors, and neglected health. The nurse monitors metabolic effects (weight, glucose, lipids, blood pressure), especially on antipsychotics, and ensures routine screenings, vaccines, and dental care are not skipped. Smoking cessation, healthy nutrition, and activity are encouraged. A critical risk is diagnostic overshadowing, wrongly attributing physical symptoms to the patient's mental illness; the nurse takes physical complaints seriously and investigates them rather than dismissing them. The nurse coordinates with primary and medical care for whole-person treatment and advocates so the patient receives the same quality of physical care as anyone else.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Monitor metabolic effects (weight, glucose, lipids, BP)",
    "Ensure routine screenings, vaccines, and dental care",
    "Encourage smoking cessation, nutrition, and activity",
    "Take physical complaints seriously (avoid diagnostic overshadowing)",
    "Coordinate with primary and medical care"
  ],
